gource
------------------------------------------
OpenGL-based 3D visualisation tool for source control repositories.

The repository is displayed as a tree where the root of the repository is the
centre, directories are branches and files are leaves. Contributors to the
source code appear and disappear as they contribute to specific files and
directories.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-2.9.0-3
  libboost_filesystem1.63-1.63.0-1
  libboost_system1.63-1.63.0-1
  libfreetype6-2.6.5-1
  libgcc1-6.4.0-1
  libGLEW1.13-1.13.0-1
  libpcre1-8.40-3
  libpng16-1.6.30-2
  libSDL2_2.0_0-2.0.5-1
  libSDL2_image2.0_0-2.0.1-1
  libstdc++6-6.4.0-1
  libtinyxml0-2.6.2-1bl3

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-13-1
  automake-9-1
  binutils-2.28-3
  cygport-0.24.1-1
  gcc-core-6.4.0-1
  gcc-g++-6.4.0-1
  make-4.2.1-2

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/acaudwell/Gource

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/acaudwell/Gource/releases/download/gource-0.47/gource-0.47.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack gource-0.47-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./gource-0.47-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/gource-0.47-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/gource-0.47-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

